verses.text_plain: Praise ye the Lord. O give thanks unto the Lord; for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.
verses.verse_html:
1Praise ye the Lord. O give thanks unto the Lord; for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever. ▼
▼ Praise…: Heb. Hallelujah

verses.text_plain: Who can utter the mighty acts of the Lord? who can shew forth all his praise?
verses.verse_html: 2Who can utter the mighty acts of the Lord? who can shew forth all his praise?

verses.text_plain: Blessed are they that keep judgment, and he that doeth righteousness at all times.
verses.verse_html: 3Blessed are they that keep judgment, and he that doeth righteousness at all times.

verses.text_plain: Remember me, O Lord, with the favour that thou bearest unto thy people: O visit me with thy salvation;
verses.verse_html: 4Remember me, O Lord, with the favour that thou bearest unto thy people: O visit me with thy salvation;

verses.text_plain: That I may see the good of thy chosen, that I may rejoice in the gladness of thy nation, that I may glory with thine inheritance.
verses.verse_html: 5That I may see the good of thy chosen, that I may rejoice in the gladness of thy nation, that I may glory with thine inheritance.

verses.text_plain: We have sinned with our fathers, we have committed iniquity, we have done wickedly.
verses.verse_html: 6We have sinned with our fathers, we have committed iniquity, we have done wickedly.

verses.text_plain: Our fathers understood not thy wonders in Egypt; they remembered not the multitude of thy mercies; but provoked him at the sea, even at the Red sea.
verses.verse_html: 7Our fathers understood not thy wonders in Egypt; they remembered not the multitude of thy mercies; but provoked him at the sea, even at the Red sea.

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless he saved them for his name’s sake, that he might make his mighty power to be known.
verses.verse_html: 8Nevertheless he saved them for his name’s sake, that he might make his mighty power to be known.

tokens.text: sake, that he might make his mighty power

verses.text_plain: He rebuked the Red sea also, and it was dried up: so he led them through the depths, as through the wilderness.
verses.verse_html: 9He rebuked the Red sea also, and it was dried up: so he led them through the depths, as through the wilderness.

tokens.text: also, and it was dried up

verses.text_plain: And he saved them from the hand of him that hated them, and redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.
verses.verse_html: 10And he saved them from the hand of him that hated them, and redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.

verses.text_plain: And the waters covered their enemies: there was not one of them left.
verses.verse_html: 11And the waters covered their enemies: there was not one of them left.

verses.text_plain: Then believed they his words; they sang his praise.
verses.verse_html: 12Then believed they his words; they sang his praise.

verses.text_plain: They soon forgat his works; they waited not for his counsel:
verses.verse_html:
13They soon forgat his works; they waited not for his counsel: ▼
▼ They soon…: Heb. They made haste, they forgat

footnotes.body_text: ▼ They soon…: Heb. They made haste, they forgat
footnotes.body_html: ▼ They soon…: Heb. They made haste, they forgat

verses.text_plain: But lusted exceedingly in the wilderness, and tempted God in the desert.
verses.verse_html:
14But lusted exceedingly in the wilderness, and tempted God in the desert. ▼
▼ lusted…: Heb. lusted a lust

footnotes.body_html: ▼ lusted…: Heb. lusted a lust

verses.text_plain: And he gave them their request; but sent leanness into their soul.
verses.verse_html: 15And he gave them their request; but sent leanness into their soul.

verses.text_plain: They envied Moses also in the camp, and Aaron the saint of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16They envied Moses also in the camp, and Aaron the saint of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, and covered the company of Abiram.
verses.verse_html: 17The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, and covered the company of Abiram.

verses.text_plain: And a fire was kindled in their company; the flame burned up the wicked.
verses.verse_html: 18And a fire was kindled in their company; the flame burned up the wicked.

verses.text_plain: They made a calf in Horeb, and worshipped the molten image.
verses.verse_html: 19They made a calf in Horeb, and worshipped the molten image.

verses.text_plain: Thus they changed their glory into the similitude of an ox that eateth grass.
verses.verse_html: 20Thus they changed their glory into the similitude of an ox that eateth grass.

verses.text_plain: They forgat God their saviour, which had done great things in Egypt;
verses.verse_html: 21They forgat God their saviour, which had done great things in Egypt;

verses.text_plain: Wondrous works in the land of Ham, and terrible things by the Red sea.
verses.verse_html: 22Wondrous works in the land of Ham, and terrible things by the Red sea.

verses.text_plain: Therefore he said that he would destroy them, had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach, to turn away his wrath, lest he should destroy them.
verses.verse_html: 23Therefore he said that he would destroy them, had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach, to turn away his wrath, lest he should destroy them.

verses.text_plain: Yea, they despised the pleasant land, they believed not his word:
verses.verse_html:
24Yea, they despised the pleasant land, they believed not his word: ▼
▼ the pleasant…: Heb. a land of desire

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the pleasant…: Heb. a land of desire
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the pleasant…: Heb. a land of desire

verses.text_plain: But murmured in their tents, and hearkened not unto the voice of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 25But murmured in their tents, and hearkened not unto the voice of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Therefore he lifted up his hand against them, to overthrow them in the wilderness:
verses.verse_html:
26Therefore he lifted up his hand against them, to overthrow them in the wilderness: ▼
▼ to overthrow: Heb. to make them fall

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to overthrow: Heb. to make them fall
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to overthrow: Heb. to make them fall

verses.text_plain: To overthrow their seed also among the nations, and to scatter them in the lands.
verses.verse_html:
27To overthrow their seed also among the nations, and to scatter them in the lands. ▼
▼ To overthrow: Heb. To make them fall

footnotes.body_text: ▼ To overthrow: Heb. To make them fall
footnotes.body_html: ▼ To overthrow: Heb. To make them fall

verses.text_plain: They joined themselves also unto Baal–peor, and ate the sacrifices of the dead.
verses.verse_html: 28They joined themselves also unto Baal–peor, and ate the sacrifices of the dead.

verses.text_plain: Thus they provoked him to anger with their inventions: and the plague brake in upon them.
verses.verse_html: 29Thus they provoked him to anger with their inventions: and the plague brake in upon them.

verses.text_plain: Then stood up Phinehas, and executed judgment: and so the plague was stayed.
verses.verse_html: 30Then stood up Phinehas, and executed judgment: and so the plague was stayed.

verses.text_plain: And that was counted unto him for righteousness unto all generations for evermore.
verses.verse_html: 31And that was counted unto him for righteousness unto all generations for evermore.

verses.text_plain: They angered him also at the waters of strife, so that it went ill with Moses for their sakes:
verses.verse_html: 32They angered him also at the waters of strife, so that it went ill with Moses for their sakes:

verses.text_plain: Because they provoked his spirit, so that he spake unadvisedly with his lips.
verses.verse_html: 33Because they provoked his spirit, so that he spake unadvisedly with his lips.

verses.text_plain: They did not destroy the nations, concerning whom the Lord commanded them:
verses.verse_html: 34They did not destroy the nations, concerning whom the Lord commanded them:

verses.text_plain: But were mingled among the heathen, and learned their works.
verses.verse_html: 35But were mingled among the heathen, and learned their works.

verses.text_plain: And they served their idols: which were a snare unto them.
verses.verse_html: 36And they served their idols: which were a snare unto them.

verses.text_plain: Yea, they sacrificed their sons and their daughters unto devils,
verses.verse_html: 37Yea, they sacrificed their sons and their daughters unto devils,

verses.text_plain: And shed innocent blood, even the blood of their sons and of their daughters, whom they sacrificed unto the idols of Canaan: and the land was polluted with blood.
verses.verse_html: 38And shed innocent blood, even the blood of their sons and of their daughters, whom they sacrificed unto the idols of Canaan: and the land was polluted with blood.

verses.text_plain: Thus were they defiled with their own works, and went a whoring with their own inventions.
verses.verse_html: 39Thus were they defiled with their own works, and went a whoring with their own inventions.

verses.text_plain: Therefore was the wrath of the Lord kindled against his people, insomuch that he abhorred his own inheritance.
verses.verse_html: 40Therefore was the wrath of the Lord kindled against his people, insomuch that he abhorred his own inheritance.

verses.text_plain: And he gave them into the hand of the heathen; and they that hated them ruled over them.
verses.verse_html: 41And he gave them into the hand of the heathen; and they that hated them ruled over them.

verses.text_plain: Their enemies also oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection under their hand.
verses.verse_html: 42Their enemies also oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection under their hand.

tokens.text: them, and they were brought into subjection

verses.text_plain: Many times did he deliver them; but they provoked him with their counsel, and were brought low for their iniquity.
verses.verse_html:
43Many times did he deliver them; but they provoked him with their counsel, and were brought low for their iniquity. ▼
▼ brought…: or, impoverished, or, weakened

footnotes.body_html: ▼ brought…: or, impoverished, or, weakened

verses.text_plain: Nevertheless he regarded their affliction, when he heard their cry:
verses.verse_html: 44Nevertheless he regarded their affliction, when he heard their cry:

verses.text_plain: And he remembered for them his covenant, and repented according to the multitude of his mercies.
verses.verse_html: 45And he remembered for them his covenant, and repented according to the multitude of his mercies.

verses.text_plain: He made them also to be pitied of all those that carried them captives.
verses.verse_html: 46He made them also to be pitied of all those that carried them captives.

tokens.text: all those that carried them captives

verses.text_plain: Save us, O Lord our God, and gather us from among the heathen, to give thanks unto thy holy name, and to triumph in thy praise.
verses.verse_html: 47Save us, O Lord our God, and gather us from among the heathen, to give thanks unto thy holy name, and to triumph in thy praise.

verses.text_plain: Blessed be the Lord God of Israel from everlasting to everlasting: and let all the people say, Amen. Praise ye the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
48Blessed be the Lord God of Israel from everlasting to everlasting: and let all the people say, Amen. Praise ye the Lord. ▼
▼ Praise…: Heb. Hallelujah
